;; kabuto 兜 — seed graph of the world's PUBLIC (listed) companies (real, PUBLIC-RECORD data only)
;; ADR-2606022000 · vocabulary: public-company-ontology.kotoba.edn (00-contracts/schemas/)
;;
;; SCOPE: a bounded illustrative slice of the world's exchange-listed companies as a kotoba EAVT
;;   knowledge graph — the COMPANY (name, ticker, exchange, LEI/ISIN, sector), its registered HQ
;;   ADDRESS, its PUBLIC corporate CONTACT, the first-class SUPPLY edges (supplier → customer) that
;;   wire the global supply chain, and a couple of BPMN PROCESS templates. The lens is SUPPLY-CHAIN
;;   RESILIENCE + corporate-power TRANSPARENCY: where production concentrates onto a single-source
;;   supplier or one jurisdiction, routed to redundancy + accountability. NOT a target-list (G2).
;;
;; SOURCING (G5): every node/edge carries :*/sourcing. Company facts (ticker, exchange, HQ, sector)
;;   are matters of public record (exchange listings, GLEIF LEI, company IR pages, filings). HQ
;;   coordinates are :representative (rounded to the campus/city). Supplier EDGES are :representative
;;   — inferred from public disclosure / supplier-list filings / press, NOT an exhaustive bill of
;;   materials; :supply.edge/criticality is a bounded estimate, NEVER a contract figure. Absence of a
;;   company = "not yet ingested", NOT "does not exist". Full GLEIF/EDGAR/exchange universe ingest is
;;   G7 Council + operator gated (millions of LEIs). :company/id reuses the tsumugi org.corp.* space.

